      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09B\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Copy all rows from the decision table into a new table `J09B_temp`, but only those where the tour identifier starts with `J09B`.\\n\\n2. Add a column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to table `J09B_temp`.\\n\\n3. Classify meter reading type in `J09B_temp` using this rule for each `HAUS`:\\n   - 1. Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `\\\"KSA\\\"` when a `HAUS` has less than 3 `EQUNR`. ELSE set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `\\\"EVU\\\"`.\\n\\n4. Join table `J09B_temp` with table `EABLG` using column `INSTALLATION`, enriching `J09B_temp` with the matching `EABLG` data.\\n\\n5. Join the result with tables `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER` using `EQUNR` as the join key, so that each record contains both sales and net master customer data.\\n   - (From annotation: JOIN table with `NET_MASTER` and `SALES_MASTER` table using `EQUNR`.)\\n\\n6. For each record in the joined table, compare the customer data from `SALES_MASTER` with the customer data from `NET_MASTER` and determine whether the sales customer data for that record is empty or not.\\n\\n7. For each record in the joined table, decide which customer data to use based on the comparison:\\n   - IF the sales customer data for the record is NOT empty:\\n     - Use the sales customer data table entries (`SALES_MASTER` fields) as the authoritative customer data for that record.\\n   - ELSE:\\n     - Use the net data customer table entries (`NET_MASTER` fields) as the authoritative customer data for that record.\\n\\n8. Export the final, decided dataset to a CSV file named `J09B`.\\n   - Use this column names, when exporting the file:\\n     `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\\n\\n9. Send an email with the exported CSV file to the EVU:\\n   - Use email address `meter.readings@evu.com`.\\n   - Attach the CSV file located at `file_path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>`.\\n\\n10. Delete the temporary table `J09B_temp` from the database.\\n\\n11. End the process.\"}",
            "id": "lc_82aea15a-ad80-467d-b9fa-571bf933726f"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "5fc3762e-505b-46b9-831a-9a46de48b9ef",
